e. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":29,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Baldington was born in 1353, in Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England. He died in 1430, in England, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1353–1430":"1353–1430","1361–1389":"1361–1389","1354–1393":"1354–1393","1375–1436":"1375–1436","1436":"1436","1389":"1389","1354":"1354","1353":"1353","1375":"1375","1430":"1430","1361":"1361","1393":"1393","1382":"1382","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1353–1430":"1353–1430","1361–1389":"1361–1389","1354–1393":"1354–1393","1375–1436":"1375–1436","1436":"1436","1389":"1389","1354":"1354","1353":"1353","1375":"1375","1430":"1430","1361":"1361","1393":"1393","1382":"1382","Adderbury, Oxfordshire, England":"Adderbury, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1353–1430":"1353–1430","1361–1389":"1361–1389","1354–1393":"1354–1393","1375–1436":"1375–1436","1436":"